    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nnvim tries to create XDG directories before they're needed on launch\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nOn a read-only filesystem\r\n\r\n1. Set XDG_DATA_HOME and XDG_STATE_HOME environment variables\r\n\r\n```\r\nexport XDG_DATA_HOME=\"$HOME/xdg/data\"\r\nexport XDG_STATE_HOME=\"$HOME/xdg/state\"\r\nexport NVIM_LOG_FILE=/dev/null\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Run nvim\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ nvim -i NONE\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. An error occurs\r\n\r\n```\r\nError detected while processing /opt/homebrew/Cellar/neovim/0.9.4/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/rplugin.vim[66]..function <SNR>14_LoadRemotePlugins[1]..<S\r\nNR>14_GetManifest[1]..<SNR>14_GetManifestPath:\r\nline   10:\r\nE739: Cannot create directory /root: read-only file system\r\nPress ENTER or type command to continue\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nnvim should have a launch flag that allows opening files on a read-only filesystem, without creating any files or directories.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.9.4\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno, vim 9.0.2018\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 14.2\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nApple Terminal.app\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nhomebrew",
